Program: Omnibus
Title: Worlds Apart - The Story of the Collard Family
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mhs
Last Broadcast Date: 28 October 2002
Australia's Stolen Generations describes the Aboriginal children taken from their families to be reared by white people, a policy that continued until the late 1960s. Donald and Sylvia Collard and their children talk about how they were separated, how they were reunited, and what happened in the intervening years including ill-treatment and sexual abuse. Show less